# Holter ECG Monitoring System

## Overview

This project focuses on the design and development of a Holter-based ECG monitoring system. The system collects ECG data from wearable hardware, stores the recorded signal on an SD card, and supports two-way communication with mobile applications through BLE. The software ecosystem includes mobile applications for users and doctors, as well as a PC application for visualizing ECG signals from BIN files after applying ECG noise-filtering algorithms.


```text
Holter/
|-- App/
|   |-- user_mobile_app/          # Mobile application for end users
|   `-- visualize_ecg_pc_app/     # PC application for ECG signal visualization
|-- Detect_posture/
|   |-- manual/                   # Notes and manual processing instructions
|   |-- pipeline/                 # Data analysis and training notebooks
|   |-- reports/                  # Model training reports
|   `-- requirements.txt          # Python dependencies
|-- Node_M_data_aquire/
|   `-- NODE_M_dataAquire/        # Main data acquisition firmware
|-- Node_S_new_2/
|   `-- Node_S_new_2/             # Secondary node firmware
|-- .gitignore
`-- README.rm
```
